e   while still in his s sondheim contributed the lyrics to arthur laurents’ and jerome robbins’ “west side story” music by leonard bernstein and “gypsy” music by jule styne his first produced broadway show as both composer and lyricist was “a funny thing happened on the way to the forum”  sondheim went on to create a remarkable succession of groundbreaking musicals including “company”  “follies”  “a little night music”  “sweeney todd”  and “sunday in the park with george”  it is hard to find a musical today that hasn’t been influenced by sondheim’s remaking the rules that once governed the traditional broadway musical sondheim has won every coveted award the kennedy center honors pulitzer prize multiple grammys an academy award and multiple tonys more than any other composer including a special award for lifetime achievement in the theater in  he was elected to the american academy of arts and letters the most prestigious academic society in america in  rich is an oped columnist for the new york times who has been said to “view political life through a theatrical lens” nyts  he served as the time’s chief drama critic beginning in  the year he joined the times for  years leaving the dramatic hot seat from  to  he was the times frontpage columnist for the sunday arts  leisure section before joining the times he was a founding editor of the richmond mercury and a film and television critic at time magazine his opinion matters he is a recipient of the prestigious george polk award for commentary given annually by long island university in honor of contributions to journalistic integrity and investigative reporting rich is the author of “the greatest story ever sold the decline and fall of truth from  to katrina” and “hot seat theater criticism for the new york times ” among other titles he graduated from harvard college in  where he was editorial chairman of the harvard crimson while at the crimson rich wrote a lengthy essay about the sondheim musical “follies” prebroadway run in boston it is reported the article “fascinated” director harold prince and “absolutely” intrigued sondheim who invited the undergraduate to lunch to discuss the production the evening’s event at williams college is sponsored by the president’s office the leadership studies program the program in jewish studies and the music and theatre departments end founded in  williams college is the second oldest institution of higher learning in massachusetts the college’s  students are taught by a faculty noted for the quality of their teaching and research and the achievement of academic goals includes active participation of students with faculty in their research students’ educational experience is enriched by the residential campus environment in williamstown mass which provides a host of opportunities for interaction with one another and with faculty beyond the classroom admission decisions are made regardless of a student’s financial ability and the college provides grants and other assistance to meet the demonstrated needs of all who are admitted to visit the college on the internet httpwwwwilliamsedu williams college can also be found on facebook httpwwwfacebookcomwilliamscollege and twitter httptwittercomwilliamscollege end williams college honors nine students as gaudino fellows art historian samuel edgerton’s new book looks at how linear perspective changed our vision of the universe section menu office of communications menu office of communications more resourcesmedia relationscalendar guidelinesdaily messages guidelinesstyle guidefast facts about williamsvisitor informationevent calendar thu  aug object not found a reading  pm at williams college museum of art wed  aug summer seminar  pm at williams college museum of art thu  aug the osmothèque  pm at williams college museum of art thu  aug seed library  pm at williams college museum of art subscribe » williams calendar » stephen sondheim’s into the woods – office of communications skip to content menu